snippet.textDisplay:
Gib wasn't necessarily "Bad" overall, his main downfall was simply his footwork and stance especially against someone much taller than him. Before his first knock down he slipped up whilst he was backing away from Jake which was the first sign that he was fucked, and then when he failed to correct himself it was over.


In the past weeks and months, Gib got the reputation as the mad lad, the insane guy who will just charge in and take everything and doesn't care. Which proved to be true as he did throw some decent punches and constantly pulled himself closer to Jake. But it's not a good tactic when his stance was so poor and he was fighting a larger opponent. He could have probably continued on for multiple rounds and he'd have constantly pulled himself back up and continued along, but as the rules say three knock downs and you're out for your own safety. Gib must have felt pressured to go along with his insane guy persona and it failed him. Compare Deji vs Jake to this, Deji rocked Jake multiple times by charging in, but the reason he managed to stay up so long was due to his decent defence and stance which he combined with his violent bursts, wheras Gib was entirely violent burst.


In terms of Jake Paul vs JJ, I think unless JJ corrects himself from the sloppy style of his last fight, Jake will win. Jake doesn't have those nerves, his meditation pre-fight, his calmness and his experience with being on TV shows, giant concerts and fighting in front of huge crowds multiple times before he can stay calm and collected during the fight. Something which KSI seemed to lack on the last fight where he went awfully wild against Logan.


Of course, I'll support KSI in the upcoming fight if it happens, same as how I supported Gib here. But I think that Jake has the advantage and I predict he would win it like I did with this one. Honestly I think a better fight would be Jake vs Deji 2. Deji and Jake despite being the younger smaller brothers seem to be the better fighters in the two families. Deji rocked Jake despite not having much of a camp at all, now imagine if he had a full camp, with such motivation as to avenge his man Gib, it would be fun to watch.
